## Print Products — Desk Mats

Desk mats are OIS's highest-margin product. All use sublimation printing (edge-to-edge, dye-into-material). Manufactured by Spoke.

### Small — 12 × 18 inches

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Print area | 12″ × 18″ |
| Thickness | 4mm |
| Aspect ratio | 2:3 |
| Pixels at 300 DPI | 3,600 × 5,400 |
| Pixels at 200 DPI | 2,400 × 3,600 |

### Medium — 12 × 22 inches

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Print area | 12″ × 22″ |
| Thickness | 3mm |
| Aspect ratio | ~6:11 |
| Pixels at 300 DPI | 3,600 × 6,600 |
| Pixels at 200 DPI | 2,400 × 4,400 |

### Large — 15.5 × 31.5 inches

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Print area | 15.5″ × 31.5″ |
| Thickness | 3mm |
| Aspect ratio | ~1:2 |
| Pixels at 300 DPI | 4,650 × 9,450 |
| Pixels at 200 DPI | 3,100 × 6,300 |

**Notes:** The large desk mat is the most pixel-hungry product in the OIS catalog. A 9,450px-wide file is the target. The 15,000 × 9,000 master canvas covers this. At typical arm's-length viewing distance (24–30 inches), 200 DPI is visually indistinguishable from 300 DPI — so 6,300 × 3,100 is the practical minimum.

Sublimation prints darker and less saturated than screen. Push colors slightly brighter.

