## Print Products — Posters & Prints (Unframed)

Enhanced Matte Paper. Digital inkjet printing (giclée quality). 189 g/m² paper, 10.3 mil thick, 94% opacity. Manufactured by Printful.

Available in 14 sizes from 5×7 through 24×36. OIS currently sells three:

### 10 × 10 inches (Square)

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Print area | 10″ × 10″ |
| Aspect ratio | 1:1 |
| Pixels at 300 DPI | 3,000 × 3,000 |

### 18 × 24 inches (Portrait)

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Print area | 18″ × 24″ |
| Aspect ratio | 3:4 |
| Pixels at 300 DPI | 5,400 × 7,200 |
| Pixels at 200 DPI | 3,600 × 4,800 |

### 24 × 36 inches (Portrait)

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Print area | 24″ × 36″ |
| Aspect ratio | 2:3 |
| Pixels at 300 DPI | 7,200 × 10,800 |
| Pixels at 200 DPI | 4,800 × 7,200 |

**Notes:** Posters use digital inkjet — the most color-accurate method. Stay in sRGB for these exports rather than CMYK. Large posters (18×24 and up) are viewed from 3+ feet, so 200 DPI is the practical quality threshold. See [DPI by Viewing Distance](#dpi-by-viewing-distance).

Portrait-orientation posters from landscape source art require either pre-planned composition, creative cropping, or a separate portrait version. This cannot be solved at export time — it must be designed at the sketch stage.

