## File Naming Convention

Consistent naming prevents mix-ups when managing dozens of exports from a single painting.

**Structure:**

`[ArtworkTitle]_[ProductType]_[Dimensions]_[ColorMode]_v[##].png`

**Examples:**

- `MoonlitForest_DeskMat_15x31_CMYK_v01.png`
- `MoonlitForest_Poster_10x10_sRGB_v01.png`
- `MoonlitForest_YTBanner_2560x1440_sRGB_v01.png`
- `MoonlitForest_Master_15000x9000_RGB.psd`

**Rules:**

- Underscores, not spaces
- Leading zeros on version numbers (v01, v02)
- ISO dates if needed: YYYYMMDD
- Keep filenames under 50 characters where possible
- Never edit the exports — return to the master file for changes, then re-export

---

## Delivery Folder Structure

When delivering to OIS, organize files as follows:

```
ProjectName/
├── Source/          (master PSD/TIFF, all layers, RGB)
├── Print/           (flattened, CMYK where needed, per product)
├── Digital/         (sRGB, web-optimized, social crops)
├── Overlays/        (1920×1080 PNG-32, sRGB, transparent)
└── Reference/       (mockups, crop guides, notes)
```

Per OIS collaborator contracts, source files (PSD/native format with layers) are required deliverables alongside finished exports.

---

## Export Checklist

Run through this before delivering any file to OIS.

**For print products:**

- [ ] Resolution is 300 DPI (or minimum 200 DPI for large-format)
- [ ] Pixel dimensions match the target product exactly
- [ ] File is PNG (or JPEG if no transparency needed)
- [ ] CMYK conversion done from RGB master (not painted in CMYK)
- [ ] Colors pushed slightly brighter for sublimation products
- [ ] Background extends beyond safe area for full bleed
- [ ] No critical elements (text, faces, logos) near edges
- [ ] No semi-transparent effects, glows, or fade-to-transparent
- [ ] Inspected at 100% zoom for artifacts
- [ ] File named per convention

**For digital assets:**

- [ ] Exact platform dimensions (no "close enough")
- [ ] sRGB color profile
- [ ] PNG format (PNG-32 if transparency needed)
- [ ] Critical content within platform safe zones
- [ ] File size under 2 MB for thumbnails, under 6 MB for banners

**For overlays:**

- [ ] Exactly 1920 × 1080px (or current OBS canvas size)
- [ ] PNG-32 with alpha transparency
- [ ] sRGB IEC61966-2.1
- [ ] Separate elements as individual files for Stream Deck toggling
- [ ] Tested in OBS before delivery

**For all deliverables:**

- [ ] Layered source file (PSD/native) included
- [ ] Consistent file naming across all exports
- [ ] Folder structure matches delivery template
- [ ] Master RGB file preserved (never overwritten by CMYK conversion)

